source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/halloumi-with-freekeh-pilaf-595517b62310a842dc4d30c2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Preheat your oven to 200°C and put the kettle on to boil. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1%whole} into roughly ½cm pieces. Halve, then remove the core from the @bell pepper{1%whole} and chop each half into three. Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat and add the onion. Cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Stir in the @chermoula spice mix{1%packet} and @freekeh{100%g}. Add the @water{200%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{¼%tsp}. Stir and bring to the boil. Turn the heat to low, pop a #lid{} on and cook for ~{15%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat and leave for ~{5%minutes}.

> TIP: The freekeh is done when soft enough to eat, but retaining some bite.

In the meantime, drizzle a little @oil{drizzle} on a lined #baking tray{} and add the pepper pieces (skin-side down). Drizzle over the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and charred around the edges, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Remove the @pistachios{25%g} from their shells (discard the shells). Heat a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the pistachios to the pan (no oil!) and toast for a couple of mins. Remove them from the pan and set aside. Cut the @halloumi{250%g} into slices about 1cm thick. Put the @mango chutney{40%g} into a small #bowl{}.

Put your now empty frying pan back on medium-high heat (no need to wash!) and add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Smother both sides of each halloumi slice in some mango chutney, then lay in the pan. Cook until golden, about ~{3%minutes} on each side, then remove from the pan. If you have any mango chutney left, spread it on the halloumi slices after they are cooked, if not, don't worry!

Fluff up the freekeh with a #fork{} and mix in three-quarters of the mint and a small squeeze of @lemon{½}(juiced). Taste and add more lemon juice, salt or black pepper if desired. Serve the freekeh in #bowls{} with the roasted pepper and caramelised halloumi on top. Sprinkle over the pistachios and any remaining mint. Enjoy!